@startuml
title Digital Watch State Transition Diagram

[*] --> Idle

state Idle {
    state ChangingHour
    state ChangingMinutes
    state AlarmHour
    state AlarmMinutes
    state LightOn
}

Idle : entry / Display Initial Time and Alarm Status
ChangingHour : entry / Increase Hours while adjusting time settings
ChangingMinutes : entry / Increase Minutes while adjusting time settings
AlarmHour : entry / Increase Alarm Hours
AlarmMinutes : entry / Increase Alarm Minutes
LightOn : entry / Turn On Light when button is pressed

ChangingHour : exit / Save new hour and switch to Idle state
ChangingMinutes : exit / Save new minute and switch to Idle state
AlarmHour : exit / Save new alarm hour and switch to Idle state
AlarmMinutes : exit / Save new alarm minute and switch to Idle state
LightOn : exit / Turn Off Light when button is released

Idle --> ChangingHour : Button Pressed for Hours Adjustment
Idle --> ChangingMinutes : Button Pressed for Minutes Adjustment
Idle --> AlarmHour : Button Pressed for Alarm Hour Adjustment
Idle --> AlarmMinutes : Button Pressed for Alarm Minute Adjustment
LightOn --> LightOn : Button Pressed
LightOn --> Idle : Button Released

ChangingHour --> ChangingHour : Increase Hours beyond 23 / Wrap around to 0
ChangingMinutes --> ChangingMinutes : Increase Minutes beyond 59 / Wrap around to 0
AlarmHour --> AlarmHour : Increase Alarm Hours beyond 23 / Wrap around to 0
AlarmMinutes --> AlarmMinutes : Increase Alarm Minutes beyond 59 / Wrap around to 0

ChangingHour --> Idle : Button Released while adjusting hours
ChangingMinutes --> Idle : Button Released while adjusting minutes
AlarmHour --> Idle : Button Released while adjusting alarm hours
AlarmMinutes --> Idle : Button Released while adjusting alarm minutes

Idle --> Idle : Current Time matches Alarm Time / Trigger Alarm and switch to LightOn state
Idle --> Idle : Alarm is Off / No action taken
LightOn --> Idle : Button Pressed for Alarm Stop / Turn off Alarm and switch to Idle state
@enduml
